defaultThe BBC is designed to serve the needs and interests of the entire nation, but occasionally this causes problems. The BBC could be accused of spreading itself too thinly, or attempting to be all things to
default all people. While appealing to the nation as a whole is a key part of the BBC’s mission it should not seek to serve the needs of niche groups at the expense of serving the needs of the wider population. This is especially the case where other PSBs have re
defaultmits specifically designed to cater to these audiences.
default 
