defaultAs the largest PSB
default, funded by licence fee payers from across the country, the BBC also has a responsibility to deliver nations and regions programming. The BBC is in a strong position to do this thanks to the breadth and depth of its in house infrastructure while Channel 4 
defaultis dependent on the strengths and weaknesses of the independent suppliers in each nation and region. 
defaultUnlike the BBC Channel 4 does not produce any in-house content. Instead we commission all of our content from independent production
default companies
default. This model
default has led to massive growth in the independent production industry 
defaultsince Channel 4’s creation, 
